<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="redescription">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Length 5.3-7.8 mm, width 2.3-3.5 mm. Body color (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Habitus of Pyrrhalta taiwana Kimoto and P. viridipennis Kimoto A P. taiwana, male, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. viridipennis, male, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545541" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11D-F</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown; antenna reddish brown; elytra green but with wide yellow stripe along lateral margin, apical area more or less yellowish brown. Eyes small, interocular space 2.67-2.75 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of eye. Antennae filiform in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14A</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.7: 1.2: 1.1: 1.0: 1.0: 0.9: 0.9: 0.8: 0.7: 0.9, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.6: 2.9: 4.5: 3.9: 3.7: 3.7: 3.4: 3.5: 3.1: 3.3: 4.4; similar in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14B</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.5: 0.9: 0.9: 0.9: 0.8: 0.8: 0.7: 0.7: 0.6: 0.8, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.8: 2.1: 3.6: 4.0: 4.0: 3.6: 3.7: 3.2: 3.1: 2.9: 3.7. Pronotum and elytra convex. Pronotum 1.9-2.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
wider than long, disc with reticulate microsculpture; with dense, coarse punctures, and short pubescence, with median longitudinal and lateral depressions; lateral margins rounded, widest at middle, apical and basal margin slightly concave; anterior and posterior setiferous punctures slightly erect. Elytra elongate and broad, parallel-sided, 1.6-1.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; disc rough, with dense, fine punctures, and short pubescence. Apical spur of tibia of middle leg small and curved (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14M</figureCitation>
), and tarsomere I not modified in males. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14C, D</figureCitation>
) slender in dorsal view, 7.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, asymmetric, curved at apical 1/7, apically narrowed, apex broadly rounded; ostium large, not covered by membrane; straight but strongly curved near base in lateral view, slightly curved near apex, apex narrowly rounded; two endophallic sclerites elongate, primary sclerite longer and 0.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as aedeagus, apex with several fine teeth; secondary sclerite small, 0.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the longer sclerite. Only apices of gonocoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14J</figureCitation>
) sclerotized, elongate, with several short setae near apex, and four long setae near apex. Ventrite VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14I</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized, strongly broadened near apex, outer sides strongly curved, several short setae along apical margin and bearing cluster of long setae medially, spiculum long. Receptacle of spermatheca (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14N</figureCitation>
) very swollen; pump short and strongly curved; sclerotized proximal spermathecal duct wide and short. Apical margin of abdominal ventrite V moderately concave medially, with deep, indistinctly margined depression at middle in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14L</figureCitation>
); slightly concave, with median, longitudinal internal ridge in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
